quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  41,33,"And who is better in speech than he who summoneth Unto Allah, and worketh righteously, and saith: verily I am one of the Muslims"
  41,34,"Nor can good and evil be equal. Repel thou evil with that which is goodly then behold he between whom and thee there was enmity, will be as though he was a warm friend"
  41,35,And none attaineth that except those who are patient; and none attaineth that except the owner of mighty good fortune
  41,36,"And if there inciteth thee an incitement from the Satan then seek refuge in Allah. Verily He! He is the Hearer, the Knower"
  41,37,"And of His signs are the night and the day and the sun and the moon. So prostrate not yourselves Unto the sun nor the moon. but prostrate yourselves Unto Allah who hath created them, if it is He alone whom ye are worshipping"
  41,38,"And if they grow stiff-necked, then verily those who are with thy Lord, hallow Him night and day, and they weary not"
  41,39,"And of His signs is that thou beholdest the earth lowly, and when We send down thereon water, it stirreth to life and groweth. Verily He who quickeneth is the Quickener of the dead. Verily He is over everything Potent"
  41,40,Verily those who blaspheme Our revelations are not hid from Us. Is he then who will be cast into the Fire better or he who cometh secure on the Day of Resurrection? Work whatsoever ye will; Verily He is of that which ye work the Beholder
  41,41,Verily those who disbelieve in the Admonition when it cometh Unto them are themselves to blame. Verily it is a Book mighty
  41,42,"Falsehood cannot come at it from before it or behind it It, a revelation from One Wise and Praiseworthy"
  41,43,Naught is said Unto thee save that which was said Unto the apostles afore thee. Verily thy Lord is Owner of forgiveness and Owner of afflictive chastisement
  41,44,"And had We made it a recital in a foreign tongue, they would have surely said: wherefore are the verses thereof not detailed? A foreign tongue and an Arab! Say thou: Unto those who have believed it is a guidance and a healing: and those who believe not, - in their ears there is a heaviness, and Unto them it is blindness. These are they who are cried Unto from a place far-off"